parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause the motorcycle to come to an unexpected stop, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when riding in heavy traffic or at intersections.
symptoms: The engine shuts off without warning when slowing down
even when the clutch is pulled in; the engine dies randomly when idling; the motorcycle stalls intermittently
sometimes resulting in rear-ending or other accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increase the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: high idle RPM (4000-5000 RPM) when cold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and rear wheel lockup can cause loss of control, skidding, and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear wheel locking up while driving
inability to turn the rear wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A blown spark plug can cause the engine to fail to start, leaving the rider stranded, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: a strange noise is coming from the rear of the bike
the engine does not turn over.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water in the fuel tank or fuel line can cause the engine to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potentially causing damage to the engine.
symptoms: water is found in the fuel tank or fuel line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose or fallen muffler can cause noise and vibration, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
A faulty battery can cause the motorcycle to fail to start, leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: the battery is dead or faulty.
